In the INTEREST OF: B.N.C., D.C., J.C., and K.D.C., Plaintiffs, Juvenile Officer, Respondent,
v.
D.P.C. (Father), Appellant, A.D.C. (Mother), Defendant. WD 81681
Consolidated with WD 81682
WD 81683
WD 81684 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Order filed: December 18, 2018 Mary E. Barnard, for Respondent Stephen C. Pratte, for Appellant Before Division One: Lisa White Hardwick, Presiding Judge, Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Judge and Thomas N. Chapman, Judge

ORDER

PER CURIAM:

Father appeals from the judgment of the Circuit Court of Boone County terminating his parental rights to his four children. We affirm. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, we have provided the parties an unpublished memorandum setting forth the reasons for this order. Rule 84.16(b).
